Title:
NativeDump — Dump LSASS via NTAPI by hand-crafting minimal Minidump files (no MiniDumpWriteDump)

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- NativeDump is a Windows credential-access tool that dumps the LSASS process by manually constructing a valid Minidump file using only NTAPI calls from ntdll.dll, avoiding dbghelp!MiniDumpWriteDump.  
- It solves the problem of common EDR detections around standard dump APIs and full-featured dump formats by generating a minimal dump containing only the streams required by Mimikatz/Pypykatz (SystemInfo, ModuleList, Memory64List).  
- The repo documents the Minidump layout (header, stream directory, streams, memory regions) and how to populate required fields, including OS versioning and module base discovery.  
- It uses NT primitives to enable SeDebugPrivilege, open LSASS, enumerate memory regions with NtQueryVirtualMemory, and read memory with NtReadVirtualMemory.  
- Multiple “flavours” (C#, Python, Go, C/C++, BOF, etc.) include options like ntdll remapping/overwrite methods to reduce user-mode API hooking impact and optional remote exfiltration/encoding.  
- Useful primarily for Red Teams and pentesters; also relevant to Blue Teams for understanding/detecting NTAPI-based dumping and handcrafted Minidump artifacts.

Technical Focus:
- NTAPI-only LSASS dumping (ntdll.dll)
- Hand-crafted Minidump format (Header, Stream Directory, SystemInfo/ModuleList/Memory64List)
- Memory region enumeration and collection (NtQueryVirtualMemory, NtReadVirtualMemory)
- Privilege enablement via NT token APIs (SeDebugPrivilege)
- Module base/address discovery (NtQueryInformationProcess + memory reads)
- Evasion tradecraft: avoiding MiniDumpWriteDump, ntdll remap/overwrite, remote dump byte exfiltration

Use Cases:
- Dump LSASS credentials for offline parsing with Mimikatz/Pypykatz
- Evaluate/evade detections focused on dbghelp MiniDumpWriteDump usage
- Build custom dumpers in alternative languages/BOFs for operator flexibility
- Exfiltrate dump content without writing a full dump to disk (branch-dependent)
- Defensive research: create detections for NTAPI-based dumping and minimal Minidump anomalies

Keywords:
LSASS, lsass.exe, Minidump, MDMP, MiniDumpWriteDump bypass, NTAPI, ntdll.dll, NtOpenProcess, NtReadVirtualMemory, NtQueryVirtualMemory, NtQueryInformationProcess, NtAdjustPrivilegesToken, NtOpenProcessToken, SeDebugPrivilege, Memory64ListStream, ModuleListStream, SystemInfoStream, API hooking bypass, ntdll unhooking, Mimikatz, Pypykatz, BOF, EDR evasion, PPL (Protected Process Light)